title: Tompkins falls to Strake Jesuit 42-21
text: Tompkins falls to Strake Jesuit 42-21 Jimmy Galvan Sports Editor Katy Times | 0 comments After opening up its district season with a win over Seven Lakes, Tompkins headed to Crusader Stadium to take on the offensively high-powered Strake Jesuit Friday, Oct. 2. Strake Jesuit ran out to a 21-0 lead over Tompkins and cruised to a 42-21 win last Friday. Oct. 2 to move to 3-2 overall, 2-0 in district play.
